HEADWORD: Heartstruck
<hw>Heart"struck`</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rt"str⟦ucr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Driven to the heart; infixed in the mind.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧His <xex>heartstruck</xex> injuries.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Shocked with pain, fear, or remorse; dismayed;
heartstricken.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heartswelling</ent>⟦br⟧
